## Create User update form in Profile tab ##

Step 1: In users/forms.py create class UserUpdateFrom and ProfileUpdateForm
    class UserUpdateForm has fields to update username and email
    class ProfileUpdateForm has field to update profile pic

Step 2: In users/views.py, with login decorator, add profile function with request conditions
    call classes create in forms.py with valid conditions and save the changes
    Add context to view the updates

Step 3: To view the changes in profile webpage, open profile.html template, make code change as:
    {{ form|crispy }}  --> {{ u_form|crispy }}
                           {{ p_form|crispy }}

Step 4: We want to view the profile pic in home page, so in home.html, we added image under article tag
    <img class="rounded-circle article-img" src="{{ post.author.profile.image.url }}">

Step 5: To save memory, we specified the image size to 300x300 pixels
    In users/models.py, add save() method with conditions to resize the image using pillow library